Narrated in first person, "'''Out of the Closet: The Assassin's Tale'''" by [[Jennifer Roberson]] sets [[Anzat (species)|Anzati]] brain-vampire, [[Dannik Jerriko]] loose in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]]. It appeared in ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'' which was published [[December]] [[1995]] by [[Bantam Spectra]].

==Plot summary==
The ancient [[Anzat (species)|Anzati]] [[Dannik Jerriko]] is on the prowl on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], stalking prey so he can feed upon the [[Blood/Legends|blood]], [[Brain/Legends|brains]] and "soup" of his victims. He has had to make do with dregs and reprobates – not the refined meals of those truly gifted with luck or [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]. Skulking in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's palace]], he is responsible for the [[Death/Legends|deaths]] of [[Ak-Buz]] (a [[Weequay/Legends|Weequay]] [[Sail barge/Legends|sail barge]] [[Captain/Legends|captain]]) and the scullion [[Phlegmin]], though no one suspects Jerriko is the true culprit in the murders. Jerriko longs to eat the soup of [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt]] – or, better yet, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] – but he misses their departure for the [[Dune Sea/Legends|Dune Sea]].

==Continuity==
The tales of [[Phlegmin]], [[J'Quille/Legends|J'Quille]], [[Gartogg/Legends|Gartogg]], [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]], [[Barada/Legends|Barada]] and the [[Weequay/Legends|Weequay]], [[Tessek/Legends|Tessek]], and [[Buboicullaar/Legends|Bubo]] form a weaving narrative of unsolved [[Death/Legends|murders]] and a plot to [[Bomb/Legends|bomb]] [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba's]] [[Sail barge/Legends|sail barge]]. This story revealed [[Dannik Jerriko]] as the [[Assassin/Legends|murderer]].<ref name="TERC" />

